most people divide themselves/have their identities divided. I will never say I am creole first ever. Seychellois first then creole. But usually that just divides you because divide and conquer is kind of a thing since the colonialist times. I am pro union but without feeling of superiority, or connectedness to my religion /one particular kind of food. But still aware of why people would do this.

Can you please add some more categories to your studies? Race and kleptocracy are two Cultural/socioeconomic problems that causes crippling effect on living conditions of local people here in Seychelles. Give us an ability to box these type of organizations and individuals. You'll open more eyes and people can begin to ask the right questions.
